Run-18	2018	Au+Au	200 GeV	QGP and heavy flavor
Run-19	2019	Au+Au	7.7 – 62.4 GeV (Beam Energy Scan II)	QCD phase diagram, critical point search
Run-20	2020 (planned, limited due to COVID-19)	p+p, Au+Au (limited)	Various	Continued spin and QGP studies
Notes

Beam Energy Scan (BES): Runs like Run-19 focused on varying collision energies to explore the QCD phase diagram and search for the critical point.
Small Systems: Runs with p+Au, d+Au, He3+Au collisions study collective effects in small systems.
Spin Physics: Proton-proton runs with polarized beams are dedicated to understanding proton spin structure.
System Size Variation: Runs with Cu+Cu and U+U collisions explore how system size and shape affect QGP formation.
This list highlights the evolution of RHIC’s physics program, showcasing its versatility in collision species and energies to address diverse questions in nuclear and particle physics.

